President Muhammadu Buhari has Monday charged the ministerial-designates to be prepared to work laboriously to ensure they deliver optimally to Nigerians.  Speaking today at the Presidential Retreat for ministers at the Presidential Villa in Abuja, President Buhari reiterated his administration’s determination to lift 100 million Nigerians out of poverty by the end of 2023.He added that the three cardinal goals of his regime, Security, Economic revitalization and anti-corruption campaign have been successful and that efforts are ongoing to strengthen institutions.  President Buhari also urged the 43 incoming Ministers to work as a team for the full implementation of the programs and policies of his administration in order to lift Nigerians out of poverty and make the nation economically viable. He said their role will be to develop and implement policies, projects and programmes in their respective ministries, Department and agencies in line with set goals.  Earlier, the Secretary to the Government of the Federation, Mr Boss Mustapha, implored the Minister designates to work in unity with the President to improve the overall well-being of Nigerians.